         I almost never swap out spells when I'm solo'ing.  Talking about when I group.  I think my problem though, is that I like to keep arch lich ready and memmed.  I need to break myself of this luxury.  </P><P>I feel a good necro, when grouped, should be constantly swapping out spells though.  Naturally some days you are lazy, but normally I am doing everything.  I'm healing, dot'ing, mezzing, sometimes pulling, ect..ect..  It doesn't matter who is in a group.  Cleric in the group?  Oh well, I'm still healing and I dare them to ask me for manna when I'm healing for them.  Enchanter in the group?  I race to see if I can get mezz on it first.  IF there is multiple mobs and i mezz them more quickly, how much damage did I save the tank, and thus the cleric's manna?  Are there undead out and about?  Guess what.  I'm charming.  I love charming.  I'm good at charming.  Group doesn't like that I'm charming?  They will when they find out how much control I have over my pets and the increase in damage.</P><P>Basically, there is no way I can do all these things without swapping out spells.  The only thing that I HATE about grouping is the constant swapping out of spells.  But, I guess I'll just have to deal with it.  Thx for the input everyone.</P><P>&lt;img src="http://www.cmdlineninja.com/ss/xanox.jpg"&gt;<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
