         I guess it depends on your idea of fun.  There are those necros that stand up, assist to send in pet, cast splurt, sit down.  There are others that load up all group related spells to fill in holes in the group, like Degen to buff melee over 100 Sta for no loss of stats for fatigue, heal, crowd control, tank, pull.</P><P>My personal preference with a slower in the group is to load up huge aggro spells and tank with deflux, vex, vamp embrace.  Not a whole lot of swapping there.</P><P>Another favorite is to stack as many dots as I can and then FD it off.  That requires swapping cause I only use 2 slots for the dots...not including vex and deflux.</P><P>Another is to be the support caster using Degen, Heal, Mez, AC tap, pet buff, lich, snare.  That uses a bit of swapping too.</P><P>If you wanna be all that you can be, swapping is mandatory and fun.  Hotkey them spellbook pages, memorize the positions of spells in the book, and swap swap swap away.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
