        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Guys, good news for those of you who don't like swapping. It gets a lot easier when you become a little Warlock. :)<BR>Your Vexing Mordania is now optional.. Zeefers has the benefit of healing your entire group, and yourself (from liching usually, if you're tanking, of course it'll be different).<BR>Let's put it this way, my spell lineup in Seb with an avg group (no cleric, no chanter) -<BR>1 Deflux or ToN<BR>2 ST<BR>3 Insidious Retro<BR>4 FD<BR>5 QVoX<BR>6 Zeefers<BR>7 Arch-lich/Augment death (those two I do actually swap out, but every 15-20 min isn't bad for one spell swap)<BR>8 (whatever the group needs) Mind Wrack most of the time. Occasionally something else like a quick nuke (conglacion of bone) or a quick DoT (cess of corr, EB.. the rest just take too long)</P><P>So there's not much switching, there's not a lot of standing and being super active, but am I useful to my group? Hah.. considering I can carry a group without an enchanter or a cleric.. yeah, necros can be pretty useful. Now, in case Verant is reading this.. FIX MY DAMAGE AT A RAID. You know we suck, fix us. Oh, and since you played with the caster npc's that like to ice comet me now.. up my damn hp's. 'k, thx. <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205091" target="_blank"><font color=red><font size=5>Ashtaroth Solarium</font id=size5></font id=red></a><BR><i>Nec-Romancer of Innoruuk</i><BR><i>Legends of the Realm</i><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
